'''Tamizander Rey''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Commander/Legends|commander]] of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. A native of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Esseles/Legends|Esseles]] in the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Galactic Core]], Rey abandoned his role with the [[Esselian defense force]] following the [[Dissolution of the Imperial Senate/Legends|dissolution of the Imperial Senate]] shortly before the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. After joining the Rebellion, he served at the secret [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] on the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]] ice planet [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]] by [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]]. As the facility's senior [[Deck officer/Legends|deck officer]], he was responsible for overseeing all [[Hangar/Legends|docking bay]] operations. At Rey's suggestion, [[General/Legends|General]] [[Carlist Rieekan/Legends|Carlist Rieekan]] issued an order preventing any [[Starship/Legends|starship]] from leaving Hoth's surface until Echo Base's [[Deflector shield generator/Legends|energy shield]] was activated, which earned Rey the ire of many non-Rebel [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] finding themselves trapped in the base as a result. During the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]], Rey coordinated the evacuation of the base's various [[Transport/Legends|transports]].

==Biography==
===Echo Base deck officer===
{{Quote|Has Commander Skywalker reported in yet?''"<br />"''I haven't seen him. It's possible he came in through the south entrance.''"<br />"''It's ''possible?'' Why don't you go find out? It's getting dark out there.|Han Solo and Tamizander Rey|<ref name="ESB" />}}
Tamizander Rey was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] from the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core World]] [[Esseles/Legends|Esseles]], a [[Planet/Legends|planet]] highly regarded for its rich culture, celebrated museums, and technologically-advanced research facilities. Rey served as a member of the [[Esselian defense force]], a local military unit, though he resigned following the [[Dissolution of the Imperial Senate/Legends|dissolution of the Imperial Senate]] by [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Galactic Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], just prior to the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]].<ref name="Who's Who" />

[[File:HanGetsSnarkyWithDeckOfficer-TESB.png|thumb|left|300px|Han Solo questions Tamizander Rey.]]

Afterward, Rey joined the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] as a highly-skilled [[Starship/Legends|starship]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]], eventually earning an assignment to the [[Alliance High Command/Legends|Alliance High Command's]] secret [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] on the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]] ice planet [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]] by<ref name="SWE">''[[Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref> [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]],<ref name="Date">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']] to [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]].</ref> as a [[Commander/Legends|commander]]. As Echo Base's senior [[Deck officer/Legends|deck officer]], Rey was responsible for overseeing the facility's [[Hangar/Legends|docking bay]] operations in the base's main [[Hangar/Legends|hangar]], working closely with [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Romas Navander/Legends|Romas Navander]], who coordinated and relayed orders to Rebel ships from the command center. No starship landed on or departed from the ice planet without Rey's knowledge.<ref name="Who's Who" />

When [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] returned to the base after one of many routine [[Scout/Legends|scouting]] missions of the external Hoth perimeter with [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], Rey was present in the docking bay, helping to oversee the maintenance of the base's [[T-47 airspeeder/Legends|T-47 airspeeders]], dubbed "[[Snowspeeder/Legends|snowspeeders]]," by ordering a group of [[Maintenance droid/Legends|repair droids]] to assist in the difficulty Echo Base had getting the [[Airspeeder/Legends|speeders]] to operate in the planet's nighttime sub-freezing [[Temperature/Legends|temperatures]].<ref name="Freedom's Winter">{{ESBRadio|Freedom's Winter}}</ref> [[General/Legends|General]] [[Carlist Rieekan/Legends|Carlist Rieekan]], commander of the base, and [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] ordered Rey to report in to the command center as soon as Skywalker and Solo returned. When Rey attempted to direct Solo to the command center, the [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] was more interested in the condition of his [[Freighter/Legends|freighter]], the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']]. Solo was upset to discover, as he learned from Rey, that base [[Technician/Legends|technicians]] were pulled away from working on the ship to address the more dire needs of the snowspeeders.<ref name="ESB script">[[The Empire Strikes Back: The National Public Radio Dramatization|''The Empire Strikes Back'': The National Public Radio Dramatization]]</ref>

After Solo discovered later that Skywalker had failed to report in to the base after investigating a purported [[Meteorite/Legends|meteorite]] that crashed into Hoth's icy surface during their scouting mission, he questioned Rey as to whether or not Skywalker had been heard from. Rey sheepishly responded that he had not seen him but considered the possibility that Skywalker may have alternatively entered through the base's southern entrance.<ref name="ESB" /> Although not in an official position to give commands,<ref name="ESB novel">[[Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode V: The Empire Strikes Back'' novelization]]</ref> Solo ordered Rey to check on Skywalker's location, to which Rey complied, eventually discovering for himself that Skywalker was missing.<ref name="ESB" />

===Search for Skywalker and Battle of Hoth===
{{Quote|Prepare to launch snowspeeders!|Tamizander Rey, directing the departure of Rogue Group in the search for Luke Skywalker and Han Solo|<ref name="ESB script" />}}
As pilots from [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Group]] prepared to depart from the base the next morning in snowspeeders to search for Skywalker and Solo, the latter of whom had left the base just as night settled to search for his missing friend, Rey eagerly reported to Rieekan that external temperatures had reached operational limits for the speeders and that the base's [[Blast door/Legends|shield doors]] were ready to be opened. Rey proceeded to direct each Rogue's departure from the hangar.<ref name="ESB script" />

Shortly before the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]], Rey made the suggestion to General [[Pharl McQuarrie/Legends|Pharl McQuarrie]], second-in-command to Rieekan, that no ship be permitted to leave Hoth until the base's [[Deflector shield generator/Legends|shield generator]] had been activated.<ref name="Who's Who" /> Rieekan agreed with the precautionary measure,<ref name="ESB" /> effectively grounding the many non-Rebel pilots delivering supplies to Echo Base, who in turn became angry with Rey. Rey was later grievously injured during the Alliance defeat at the Battle of Hoth while coordinating the departures of the various Rebel evacuation [[Transport/Legends|transports]]. Nevertheless, he dutifully continued to oversee the evacuations. Despite the crushing Rebel defeat, a significant portion of Echo Base's personnel and equipment were able to escape the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] assault,<ref name="Who's Who" /> including thirteen of thirty [[GR-75 medium transport/Legends|GR-75 medium transports]].<ref name="ESB novel" />

==Personality and traits==
{{Quote|I joined up with the Rebels because I notice things&hellip;|Tamizander Rey|<ref name="ESB script" />}}
The increasing [[Imperialization/Legends|Imperialization]] of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], part of which included the disbanding of the [[Imperial Senate/Legends|Imperial Senate]] in 0 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|BBY]], led Tamizander Rey to join the Rebel Alliance<ref name="Who's Who" /> as a talented starship pilot.<ref name="SWE" /> As Echo Base's senior deck officer, he suggested to the base's command staff that no ship be allowed to leave Hoth until the [[Deflector shield/Legends|shield]] generator was activated despite the resulting flak he received from non-partisan pilots. During the Imperial invasion of Hoth, he dutifully proceeded to oversee the departing escape transports even after suffering serious injuries.<ref name="Who's Who" />

Rey had a particularly tumultuous relationship with Han Solo, whose brash nature often clashed with his own responsibilities as senior deck officer. Solo typically responded to Rey's requests to follow base procedure with his trademark sarcasm, neglecting a direct order to report to the command center<ref name="ESB script" /> and later ordering Rey to check on Luke Skywalker's missing status, without necessarily having the authority to do so.<ref name="ESB novel" /> When Solo snapped at Rey to quickly check on Skywalker due to Hoth's threatening nighttime cold, Rey fired back in return that he was well aware that Hoth's [[Hoth (star)/Legends|sun]] was setting, quipping that he joined the Rebellion because of his perceptive nature.<ref name="ESB script" />

==Behind the scenes==
Tamizander Rey first appeared in the [[May]] [[1980]] [[Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back (novelization)|novelization]] of [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']], written by [[Donald F. Glut]],<ref name="ESB novel" /> just prior to the film's theatrical release, in which he was played by actor [[Norman Chancer]], credited only as one of several "Other Officers."<ref name="ESB" /> The character was first identified by name in the [[November]] [[1996]] ''[[Hoth Limited]]'' expansion set of the [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]], which also provided Rey with a backstory.<ref name="Hoth Limited" />

Rey's interaction with Solo in ''The Empire Strikes Back'' novelization is much more expansive than the film. In the novelization, Rey, who is referred to as a "deck [[Sergeant/Legends|sergeant]]," is accompanied by an aide when first queried by Solo. Additionally, it is Rey who subsequently reports back to Solo that Skywalker has not returned to Echo Base through the south entrance, going on to warn Solo that Hoth's dropping nighttime temperatures would mean the [[Death/Legends|death]] of his [[Tauntaun/Legends|tauntaun]] as he exits the base to search for Skywalker.<ref name="ESB novel" /> This role is instead occupied by character [[Tigran Jamiro/Legends|Tigran Jamiro]] in the film, portrayed by actor [[Ray Hassett]], to whom Solo retorts he will "see in [[Chaos/Legends|Hell]]."<ref name="ESB" />

The Rey character holds an even greater role in ''The Empire Strikes Back'' [[The Empire Strikes Back (radio)|radio drama]] and [[The Empire Strikes Back: The National Public Radio Dramatization|dramatization script]]. The role of "Deck Officer," voiced by [[Ron Frazier]], combines the film's characters of Rey, Jamiro, [[Bren Derlin/Legends|Bren Derlin]], and [[Cal Alder/Legends|Cal Alder]] into one. The "Deck Officer" is also referred to as a "Lieutenant" both in the scene occupied by Jamiro in the film and that in which he oversees Rogue Group's morning departure to find the stranded Skywalker and Solo. Since neither Rey nor Jamiro [[canon]]ically hold the rank of lieutenant and both characters are combined into a single role, there may arise ambiguity concerning which character truly appears in the Rogue departure scene. Given that the deck officer in this scene is directing the departure of craft from the hangar, a duty more closely associated with the responsibilities of Rey,<ref name="ESB script" /><ref name="The Coming Storm">{{ESBRadio|The Coming Storm}}</ref> this article assumes that it is indeed Rey appearing in that scene.

''[[The Empire Strikes Back Storybook]]'', a 1980 illustrated children's adaptation of the film, alternatively depicts Rey's film interaction with Solo as a brief comlink exchange, rather than a face-to-face encounter. The story refers to the character only as "the deck officer."<ref name="ESB Storybook">''[[The Empire Strikes Back Storybook]]''</ref>

